00:01:23.817 --> 00:01:25.251 line:5%,start
Hi, everybody, I'm Jeff Collins,

00:01:25.351 --> 00:01:28.321 line:5%,start
and welcome back to Part 2 of
our "Dance Moms" Tell All.

00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:31.357 line:95%,end
The whole gang's back,
plus we have a couple

00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:32.992 line:95%,end
of new moms joining us.

00:01:33.093 --> 00:01:34.694 line:95%,end
Our audience has even more questions,

00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:36.696 line:95%,end
and the girls are back to perform again.

00:01:36.796 --> 00:01:39.299 line:95%,end
The Abby Lee Dance Company
has seen a lot of drama,

00:01:39.365 --> 00:01:41.668 line:95%,end
and things got really heated this season.

00:01:41.835 --> 00:01:42.936 line:95%,end
Take a look.

00:01:43.136 --> 00:01:45.738 line:95%,end
Be grateful that Sophia
has come to Pittsburgh

00:01:45.805 --> 00:01:47.073 line:95%,end
and join that group.

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:51.511 line:95%,end
It's like going from mediocre
to flying first class.

00:01:52.278 --> 00:01:54.013 line:95%,end
You are committed, and if you leave,

00:01:54.114 --> 00:01:55.815 line:95%,end
you owe her $100,000 cash.

00:01:55.882 --> 00:01:57.584 line:95%,end
Well, thank God I have $100,000.

00:01:57.650 --> 00:01:59.419 line:95%,end
Sometimes if you have nothing
interesting

00:01:59.486 --> 00:02:01.488 line:95%,end
or intelligent to say,
you should just be quiet.

00:02:01.855 --> 00:02:03.890 line:95%,end
And I won't be quiet because
I always do have something

00:02:03.957 --> 00:02:04.991 line:95%,end
interesting or intelligent.

00:02:05.158 --> 00:02:06.392 line:95%,end
I disagree on that one.

00:02:06.459 --> 00:02:07.527 line:95%,end
- Kristie.
- Yes?

00:02:07.594 --> 00:02:09.395 line:95%,end
Look at me when you're speaking.
Look at me when you talk.

00:02:09.462 --> 00:02:11.030 line:95%,end
- Excuse me?
- Excuse me.

00:02:11.097 --> 00:02:13.233 line:95%,end
- I'm looking you in the eye, bitch.
- Let's go.

00:02:13.299 --> 00:02:14.467 line:95%,end
I'm not that way.

00:02:14.534 --> 00:02:15.969 line:95%,end
You need to settle yourself down.

00:02:16.035 --> 00:02:18.872 line:95%,end
No, I don't. Do not call me a bitch
if you can't back it up.

00:02:20.073 --> 00:02:22.275 line:95%,end
After a wild and explosive season,

00:02:22.542 --> 00:02:25.078 line:95%,end
"Dance Moms" Tell All
Reunion starts right now.

00:02:25.145 --> 00:02:27.881 line:95%,end
So let's bring out the star of our show.

00:02:27.947 --> 00:02:29.883 line:95%,end
Please welcome Abby Lee Miller.

00:02:29.949 --> 00:02:31.584 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:36.689 line:95%,end
- How are you?
- I'm good.

00:02:36.756 --> 00:02:38.691 line:95%,end
- It's great to see you.
- Thank you.

00:02:38.758 --> 00:02:40.760 line:95%,end
Have a seat.
You're looking fabulous.

00:02:40.827 --> 00:02:42.729 line:95%,end
Ready to do this again?
- Thank you. Thank you.

00:02:42.829 --> 00:02:44.430 line:95%,end
Well, I guess.
- All right, let's do it.

00:02:44.497 --> 00:02:46.833 line:95%,end
With the moms walking out at
the beginning of the season,

00:02:46.933 --> 00:02:50.170 line:95%,end
it meant that there were new
moms that came into the mix.

00:02:50.503 --> 00:02:53.740 line:95%,end
How did Kristie Ray and
Jackie fit in with our group?

00:02:54.174 --> 00:02:56.776 line:95%,end
They were nice.
They were respectful.

00:02:57.010 --> 00:02:58.478 line:95%,end
They followed my rules.

00:02:58.578 --> 00:03:02.849 line:95%,end
With the other moms, I think
there was a lot of jealousy.

00:03:03.016 --> 00:03:05.351 line:95%,end
So how do you think what
went on up in the observation

00:03:05.418 --> 00:03:07.020 line:95%,end
mezzanine may have played into

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:09.055 line:95%,end
running off some of your paying customers?

00:03:09.289 --> 00:03:12.292 line:95%,end
Oh, they've been running
off customers for years.

00:03:12.659 --> 00:03:15.895 line:5%,start
Ridiculous. Critiquing
other people's children, ridiculous.

00:03:16.029 --> 00:03:17.764 line:5%,start
So do you think that
started right from the start

00:03:17.830 --> 00:03:19.699 line:5%,start
when these kids came in and
they saw how talented they were?

00:03:19.766 --> 00:03:21.134 line:95%,end
ABBY LEE MILLER: Yes.

00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:22.802 line:95%,end
Well, one of the things that
we saw pop up on the blogs

00:03:22.869 --> 00:03:24.270 line:95%,end
and people ask about was they wanted

00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:28.007 line:95%,end
to know why Sophia and Maddie didn't ever

00:03:28.074 --> 00:03:29.309 line:95%,end
compete against each other.

00:03:29.442 --> 00:03:31.711 line:95%,end
What we had planned
was for Sophia and Maddie

00:03:31.778 --> 00:03:36.849 line:95%,end
to do a tap duet, because
Sophia is an amazing tap dancer,

00:03:37.317 --> 00:03:39.552 line:95%,end
and so is Maddie and you never get


00:03:39.719 --> 00:03:41.154 line:95%,end
to see Maddie do that on the show.

00:03:41.287 --> 00:03:45.391 line:95%,end
So who is a better dancer,
Sophia or Maddie?

00:03:49.762 --> 00:03:52.232 line:95%,end
I think they're very different dancers.

00:03:52.298 --> 00:03:53.866 line:95%,end
I'm not going to sit on this stage

00:03:53.933 --> 00:03:56.102 line:95%,end
and tell you that one is
better than the other.

00:03:56.169 --> 00:03:59.706 line:95%,end
I think Sophia has had a lot
more opportunities than Maddie.

00:03:59.772 --> 00:04:05.712 line:95%,end
I think Sophia is hit it hard
and dynamic and entertaining

00:04:05.778 --> 00:04:11.217 line:95%,end
and just lights up the
stage and she blows me away.

00:04:11.684 --> 00:04:16.189 line:95%,end
Maddie, I think she hears
the music and it's passionate

00:04:16.256 --> 00:04:18.024 line:95%,end
and it comes from her heart.

00:04:18.358 --> 00:04:20.827 line:95%,end
It's not about the sass
and the hitting it hard.

00:04:20.893 --> 00:04:22.829 line:95%,end
It's about the placement.

00:04:22.929 --> 00:04:26.633 line:95%,end
And they're just so, so very different.

00:04:26.699 --> 00:04:28.167 line:95%,end
That's why I personally never wanted

00:04:28.234 --> 00:04:30.603 line:95%,end
them to go against each other
because I wanted

00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:33.139 line:95%,end
the two kids to collaborate
and learn from each other.

00:04:33.206 --> 00:04:37.543 line:95%,end
I was trying to get Maddie
to learn from Sophia,

00:04:37.677 --> 00:04:40.246 line:95%,end
and that will never happen.

00:04:40.313 --> 00:04:42.815 line:95%,end
Let's do the same comparison
with Asia and Mackenzie.

00:04:42.882 --> 00:04:44.851 line:95%,end
Who's a better dancer?

00:04:44.917 --> 00:04:46.552 line:95%,end
Asia is a rock star.

00:04:46.786 --> 00:04:48.921 line:95%,end
She's an absolutely better performer.

00:04:48.988 --> 00:04:53.026 line:95%,end
If I was to ask her about
Bob Fosse and Michael Bennett,

00:04:53.559 --> 00:04:56.562 line:95%,end
I think Mackenzie is more knowledgeable.

00:04:56.863 --> 00:04:59.532 line:95%,end
You would do something different
if Asia was your student full-time?

00:04:59.732 --> 00:05:01.067 line:95%,end
Well, Asia has learned.

00:05:01.167 --> 00:05:04.437 line:95%,end
She has improved
in the last month at my studio.

00:05:04.537 --> 00:05:07.206 line:95%,end
- Right.
- And she's conscious of her flaws.

00:05:07.273 --> 00:05:10.843 line:95%,end
She correct herself before
I even have to step in,

00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:12.879 line:95%,end
and that is a battle that I've won.

00:05:13.012 --> 00:05:14.280 line:95%,end
That's amazing. That's amazing.

00:05:14.347 --> 00:05:15.915 line:95%,end
Abby isn't that great of a teacher.

00:05:16.015 --> 00:05:19.052 line:5%,start
What did Abby really teach you?

00:05:19.118 --> 00:05:20.853 line:5%,start
Not really anything.

00:05:20.953 --> 00:05:24.824 line:95%,end
I don't think we brought
one thing home from our time

00:05:24.924 --> 00:05:27.660 line:95%,end
that we spent at ALDC that we could use.

00:05:27.727 --> 00:05:30.496 line:95%,end
And Mackenzie has realized
very quickly

00:05:30.763 --> 00:05:32.265 line:95%,end
that you have to step up to the plate.

00:05:32.432 --> 00:05:34.233 line:95%,end
- So Asia really made her step it up.
- Yes.

00:05:34.467 --> 00:05:37.904 line:95%,end
I think that Sophia rocked Maddie's world,

00:05:38.671 --> 00:05:41.240 line:95%,end
but Maddie is smart enough to figure out--

00:05:42.041 --> 00:05:44.577 line:95%,end
she used it in a positive way.

00:05:44.644 --> 00:05:46.245 line:95%,end
She was enlightened.

00:05:46.312 --> 00:05:48.548 line:95%,end
- I think Mackenzie did the same thing.
- Well, that's amazing.

00:05:48.781 --> 00:05:50.850 line:95%,end
Let's take some questions
from the audience for Abby.

00:05:51.050 --> 00:05:52.819 line:95%,end
Do you think the other
dance moms are jealous

00:05:52.885 --> 00:05:55.388 line:95%,end
of Kristie Ray because of
her physical attributes?

00:05:55.988 --> 00:05:58.758 line:95%,end
Oh! Yes.
So am I. [laughter]

00:05:59.058 --> 00:06:01.361 line:95%,end
My goodness.
Her waist is this big.

00:06:02.295 --> 00:06:03.563 line:95%,end
Way up here.

00:06:03.629 --> 00:06:06.366 line:95%,end
She's exquisite
and she's exotic and she's fun.

00:06:06.499 --> 00:06:07.700 line:95%,end
Pretty, pretty, girl.

00:06:07.834 --> 00:06:10.570 line:95%,end
- That was nice.
- Thank you, Abby.

00:06:10.636 --> 00:06:12.138 line:95%,end
Asia Ray's mom is here.

00:06:12.205 --> 00:06:14.240 line:95%,end
Please welcome Kristie Ray.

00:06:14.440 --> 00:06:16.275 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:06:17.243 --> 00:06:19.011 line:95%,end
- Look at that dress.
ABBY LEE MILLER: Whoa.

00:06:19.145 --> 00:06:21.848 line:95%,end
- How are you? Come sit.
- How are you? Look, I get the hug.

00:06:22.014 --> 00:06:23.282 line:95%,end
Yeah.

00:06:23.349 --> 00:06:25.184 line:95%,end
- I don't want to mess up her makeup.
- How are you?

00:06:25.318 --> 00:06:26.786 line:95%,end
- Wonderful.
- Wow.

00:06:26.853 --> 00:06:28.354 line:95%,end
It's been a long time
since we've seen you.

00:06:28.421 --> 00:06:29.422 line:95%,end
Yes.

00:06:29.522 --> 00:06:31.891 line:95%,end
We first met you at Abby's
Ultimate Dance Competition

00:06:31.958 --> 00:06:33.226 line:95%,end
back in the summer.
- Mm-hmm.

00:06:33.292 --> 00:06:35.294 line:95%,end
So when you went to
Abby's studio in Pittsburgh,

00:06:35.395 --> 00:06:38.664 line:95%,end
how was it fitting in with the moms?

00:06:38.731 --> 00:06:43.169 line:95%,end
Well, first I want to
say that Asia loves Abby

00:06:43.236 --> 00:06:47.740 line:95%,end
and I'm here because I appreciate Abby.

00:06:48.074 --> 00:06:50.843 line:95%,end
And being an outsider coming in here,

00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:53.146 line:95%,end
I knew an outsider was never going to fit

00:06:53.413 --> 00:06:56.916 line:95%,end
in the world of these moms
that have been a group for so long.

00:06:57.250 --> 00:07:00.019 line:95%,end
But I'm not here to actually make friends.

00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:03.222 line:95%,end
I'm here to move my daughter
forward, get the training

00:07:03.289 --> 00:07:04.524 line:95%,end
that she needs.

00:07:04.590 --> 00:07:07.827 line:95%,end
And Asia gravitates
towards strong, tough love

00:07:07.894 --> 00:07:12.465 line:95%,end
that some may disagree with,
and since she's been with Abby,

00:07:12.565 --> 00:07:14.434 line:95%,end
I've seen a tremendous difference.

00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:17.437 line:95%,end
So right now, fitting in
is not an issue with me


00:07:17.503 --> 00:07:18.838 line:95%,end
because I'm doing it for Asia.

00:07:18.905 --> 00:07:20.072 line:95%,end
So tell me this.

00:07:20.139 --> 00:07:21.741 line:95%,end
Which one of the moms at
the Abby Lee Dance Company

00:07:21.808 --> 00:07:23.176 line:95%,end
did you have the most trouble with?

00:07:23.242 --> 00:07:25.745 line:95%,end
I think they all have issues with me

00:07:26.112 --> 00:07:28.748 line:95%,end
that maybe they just don't understand
why I'm here.

00:07:28.815 --> 00:07:32.919 line:95%,end
I think they think there's
some ulterior motive,

00:07:33.319 --> 00:07:35.087 line:95%,end
something else going on.

00:07:35.154 --> 00:07:38.991 line:95%,end
Well, most people want to
leave Pittsburgh and go to LA

00:07:40.359 --> 00:07:41.894 line:95%,end
for their dance career.

00:07:41.961 --> 00:07:44.497 line:95%,end
Like there's not many
opportunities in Pittsburgh.

00:07:44.564 --> 00:07:46.098 line:95%,end
I mean, let's be real.

00:07:46.165 --> 00:07:48.501 line:95%,end
So it just seems odd.

00:07:48.601 --> 00:07:50.203 line:95%,end
I see what she sees.

00:07:50.269 --> 00:07:56.042 line:95%,end
And there's 181 dance studios
in Orange County, California alone.

00:07:56.108 --> 00:07:59.011 line:95%,end
She can get great training right here.

00:07:59.078 --> 00:08:01.747 line:95%,end
But Asia worked with me in the one on one

00:08:01.848 --> 00:08:03.616 line:95%,end
private tutoring session.

00:08:03.749 --> 00:08:08.154 line:95%,end
And in that 30 minutes, I fix things.

00:08:08.721 --> 00:08:11.357 line:95%,end
And maybe I'm the right teacher for Asia.

00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:12.792 line:95%,end
- Yeah. She soaked it up.
ABBY LEE MILLER: Yes.

00:08:12.859 --> 00:08:14.560 line:95%,end
But it's also Abby teaches hard,

00:08:14.660 --> 00:08:16.262 line:95%,end
so it prepares them for the real world.

00:08:16.362 --> 00:08:18.531 line:95%,end
Let me ask you something.
Do you think these moms are scared of you?

00:08:20.233 --> 00:08:21.667 line:95%,end
No. I don't think
they're scared of me.

00:08:21.834 --> 00:08:24.237 line:95%,end
Like we said something about
how Asia cries

00:08:24.303 --> 00:08:26.506 line:95%,end
and it was like she was going to beat
the [bleep] out of Kristie.

00:08:26.973 --> 00:08:29.242 line:95%,end
And we were like, whoa.
Hold back.

00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:33.079 line:95%,end
They know that I'm not a pushover
and they know that I stand my ground.

00:08:33.212 --> 00:08:37.383 line:95%,end
And I do, you know,
have a slight snappiness.

00:08:37.483 --> 00:08:40.553 line:95%,end
I mean-- [laughs] un poquito.
- Un poquito.

00:08:40.720 --> 00:08:43.523 line:95%,end
But you know what, I don't like something
that I feel passion about

00:08:43.589 --> 00:08:45.691 line:95%,end
and have it like twisted or downplayed.

00:08:45.758 --> 00:08:48.427 line:95%,end
And I think that, in some cases,
they try to do that.

00:08:48.661 --> 00:08:52.365 line:95%,end
I didn't think that she would
rattle anybody's nerves

00:08:52.431 --> 00:08:54.667 line:95%,end
because Asia is seven.

00:08:54.734 --> 00:08:56.435 line:95%,end
What does little Asian matter?

00:08:56.502 --> 00:08:59.472 line:95%,end
And then we went to a
competition not too long ago

00:08:59.939 --> 00:09:02.441 line:95%,end
and Maddie won and Asia was second.

00:09:02.875 --> 00:09:05.411 line:95%,end
- She beat a lot of those older kids.
- Wow, that's amazing.

00:09:05.578 --> 00:09:08.581 line:95%,end
So what does Asia bring to your
studio that no other kid has?

00:09:08.648 --> 00:09:14.987 line:95%,end
[laughs] Energy, excitement,
and a whole lot of sass.

00:09:15.121 --> 00:09:18.157 line:95%,end
She does, I mean, I remember her
from Abby's Ultimate Dance Competition.

00:09:18.257 --> 00:09:19.625 line:95%,end
The kid's bouncing off
the walls like 24/7.

00:09:19.692 --> 00:09:24.797 line:95%,end
She is. She is.
She has a tremendous work ethic.

00:09:24.864 --> 00:09:29.201 line:95%,end
As far as a student goes
and feeding off of her energy, I love it.

00:09:29.402 --> 00:09:33.072 line:95%,end
All right. Our first solo of the evening
